cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CE

This paper deals with resource allocation in fog computing, which involves distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes a market-based approach, which falls under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT). The use of fog computing for networking and communication also makes cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a likely category. The paper also deals with control and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a privacy-preserving distributed algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
